properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 23 at 9:03PM CST until January 24 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Light to Moderate Snow Expected Southeast Overnight...

.Low pressure in Missouri will spread snow into southeast Iowa
overnight with up to 3 to 4 inches by sunrise Friday
morning.Though little wind is anticipated, roads will be impacted
during the morning commute.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches
with isolated totals to 5 inches.

* WHERE...Southeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until noon CST Friday though most of the snow will fall
overnight to about 7 am with lighter snowfall thereafter.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST FRIDAY
